1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:11,633
<i> Sorry?</i>

2
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:14,200
<i>The truth is, that was
my first kiss earlier.</i>

3
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:16,067
<i>But if you were already
pissed off with me earlier,</i>

4
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,300
<i> why did you do that?</i>

5
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,867
<i> Maybe you're just stupid.</i>

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:20,867
<i> What are you talking about?</i>

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,467
<i> Because Vince, the truth is,</i>

8
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:25,267
<i>I talked to Allan
to make you jealous.</i>

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:26,467
<i> Isn't it obvious?</i>

10
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:27,633
<i> I like you too.</i>

11
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:29,500
<i> Yes!</i>

12
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:32,100
<i>Sir, I had a hunch that
the killer might be outside.</i>

13
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:33,833
<i>Suddenly, a bystander ran away.</i>

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,333
<i>- Hey!
- Hey, stop!</i>

15
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:36,567
<i> Follow him, I'll go around!</i>

16
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> Hey, stop!</i>

17
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,033
<i> Where? Did you catch it?</i>

18
00:00:40,167 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>- No, Sir.
- What?</i>

19
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,667
<i>There are two of you,
and yet he got away?</i>

20
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:44,100
<i> Submit a report tomorrow.</i>

21
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:50,100
<i>Well, Attorney, make sure that
bastard doesn't get anything.</i>

22
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:51,100
<i> Do you understand?</i>

23
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:51,933
<i> Yes, Madam.</i>

24
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,133
<i> I'll do it right away.</i>

25
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,267
<i> Listen, Enriquez.</i>

26
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,467
<i>You'll have a desk job
until further notice.</i>

27
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,733
<i>We have a lot of
unsolved cases, Chief.</i>

28
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,300
<i>I don't think it's right for you
to just assign me to a desk job.</i>

29
00:01:01,433 --> 00:01:02,333
<i> You're right.</i>

30
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:04,100
<i>That's why I asked for
additional support</i>

31
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:05,100
<i> from the other station.</i>

32
00:01:05,233 --> 00:01:06,267
<i> She's here.</i>

33
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:10,567
What do you want to learn
from me now,

34
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,833
- because I have it all?
- Where is Major Flores?

35
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:14,233
In the office.

36
00:01:14,367 --> 00:01:15,300
Lieutenant Samson?

37
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:22,167
Lieutenant Samson...

38
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,600
What are you doing here?

39
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:28,767
Lieutenant Paloma and I
are assigned here for now.

40
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:32,667
That means Station 12
will finally solve a case.

41
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,967
I like your confidence.

42
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:43,200
But admit it,
that's why you're here,

43
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:47,667
you want to do OJT with me.

44
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:50,433
You know, I like
your confidence, huh?

45
00:01:50,567 --> 00:01:52,600
That's why you're so popular
at our station...

46
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:54,133
Oh, did you hear that?

47
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:58,833
That you were rejected
by the Mayor's girlfriend.

48
00:02:03,667 --> 00:02:05,333
Samson.

49
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:07,067
- Chief.
- Welcome to Station 12.

50
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:07,900
Thank you.

51
00:02:08,033 --> 00:02:09,233
Where's Paloma?

52
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:12,067
He's just taking care of
something, but he's on his way.

53
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,267
Let's go to my office.

54
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,567
How's that?

55
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,267
I'm excited to work with you.

56
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:22,567
How's that, Bobby?

57
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:24,367
It seems like we'll be seeing
each other often.

58
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,500
Did you hear that?

59
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:34,967
They say I'm popular
at their station.

60
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:39,633
Oh, okay, back to work,
back to work!

61
00:03:11,633 --> 00:03:12,667
Vince, oh.

62
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,667
Look, oh.

63
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:16,067
It's so early,
and he's busy fantasizing.

64
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,700
That's right!

65
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:21,900
Dude, what I'm doing
is not a fantasy anymore.

66
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:23,067
What's that?

67
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,867
Does that mean something
happened to you and Faye?

68
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Hey...

69
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:27,433
Hey, you're really rude,
aren't you?

70
00:03:27,567 --> 00:03:28,600
Don't be like that.

71
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:32,333
What is it? Tell me!

72
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:35,900
Dude, Faye has
confessed to me.

73
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:39,800
What?

74
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:41,800
That she still likes me, too.

75
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,833
Hey, she's lying.

76
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:44,867
Hey!

77
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,367
I'd believe a politician
more than you.

78
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,500
Liar!

79
00:03:48,633 --> 00:03:51,733
- I don't care if you don't.
- There!

80
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:53,200
That's still a fantasy.

81
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:54,633
<i>I'll invite you to Glen's
oath-taking on Monday?</i>

82
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:57,667
There. Look.

83
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:01,467
Wow!

84
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,533
It seems like you've got
all the luck, Vince.

85
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:04,733
You should share.

86
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:07,500
Hey, you've been undercover,

87
00:04:07,633 --> 00:04:09,167
and now you'll be part
of the first fam...

88
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:10,767
- You're so lucky!
- That's right.

89
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:11,867
Vince, you should treat us!

90
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,567
Oh, that's right, let's go!

91
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:14,933
Okay, go get what you want
from the store.

92
00:04:15,067 --> 00:04:15,800
That's right!

93
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:17,933
Miss, he'll pay for it, right?

94
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,400
Faye!

95
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:24,233
Oh, Glen?

96
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:28,100
Did you see Mommy?

97
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:32,067
She went out, but she didn't
tell me where she was going.

98
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:35,567
Okay, well, I was going to
discuss something with her

99
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:36,900
regarding the oathtaking.

100
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,733
- Glen.
- What?

101
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:42,567
Is it okay if I bring
a plus one?

102
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,133
Will I like that?

103
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:51,900
I'm sure if Daddy
were still alive,

104
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:55,233
I'm sure he would like
this guy too.

105
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:58,767
If it makes you happy, okay.

106
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,267
I'm excited to meet him.

107
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,667
Thank you, Glen.

108
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:11,167
- Wow, delicious, Dude.
- What? Are you okay now?

109
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,533
- Hey!
- Nothing beats free snacks.

110
00:05:13,667 --> 00:05:14,400
Cheers, bro, cheers.

111
00:05:14,533 --> 00:05:15,300
This is delicious.
Delicious, oh.

112
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,833
- Hey, Dude.
- Dude, how are you?

113
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:22,133
- What's up?
- Bro, Vince is treating us.

114
00:05:22,267 --> 00:05:23,133
He's in a good mood!

115
00:05:23,267 --> 00:05:24,133
You should ask him
to treat you.

116
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:25,767
Really? Wait, what's up?

117
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:27,100
Is it your birthday?

118
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:29,367
Oh, no.

119
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,200
Well, didn't he win
over you with Faye?

120
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:33,500
But, man, good job.

121
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:34,700
- Thank you, thank you.
- You're welcome.

122
00:05:36,167 --> 00:05:38,333
Oh, so what's up?
What's your plan with Faye?

123
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:41,867
She invited me to her
brother's oath-taking.

124
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,367
<i> But this egg is better, oh.</i>

125
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:45,967
Is that so? Do you have
something to wear?

126
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,333
That's the thing, Bro.

127
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:49,000
I have nothing to wear.

128
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:51,767
I can lend you some.

129
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:52,800
Really?

130
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,267
Of course! We're partners.

131
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,433
You, of all people.

132
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:56,500
Wow, Dude, thanks!

133
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:57,500
No problem.

134
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:58,533
Bro, I have something to wear!

135
00:05:58,667 --> 00:06:00,033
I already have something
to wear, Dude!

136
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:04,667
Thank you, man.
Thank you, thank you.

137
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:05,933
Partner.

138
00:06:06,067 --> 00:06:06,967
Thank you, bro.

139
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,533
Welcome to Station 12.

140
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:12,600
Thank you very much
for the opportunity, Chief.

141
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:15,900
You can count on
Lieutenant Paloma and I.

142
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:18,533
- Thank you.
- What is our first assignment?

143
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:22,633
Since you were the ones
who caught a fugitive,

144
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:26,000
I will assign Mateo Ramos
to you.

145
00:06:26,133 --> 00:06:28,000
His case is robbery,

146
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:31,567
and he is the only one
who escaped with Mandong Warak.

147
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:34,000
I thought, Chief, we need
to review the events

148
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:37,900
that have happened here
in Calabari since Mateo escaped.

149
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:39,233
That's right.

150
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:41,333
Just cross-reference that.

151
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:44,900
Maybe Mateo is the one
behind of those.

152
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,100
Chief, just in case,

153
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:48,700
who should we get
the record from?

154
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:51,467
From Enriquez.

155
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,433
From Sergeant Enriquez?

156
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:54,767
Yes.

157
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:58,267
Why? Doesn't she have
any other cases?

158
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:01,467
None because she's doing
desk duty right now.

159
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,700
Thank you.

160
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:12,567
Lieutenant Conde.

161
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,967
Enriquez, have you eaten yet?

162
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:18,867
Come on, let's eat first.

163
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:22,500
So, how are you?

164
00:07:22,633 --> 00:07:25,567
Here, I got scolded.

165
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,867
I'm on desk duty
until further notice.

166
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:32,933
Can I talk to you?

167
00:07:33,067 --> 00:07:34,167
Sure. What is that?

168
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:37,633
I just wanted
to ask you something.

169
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:42,467
I just wanted to know
if you told Chief thay

170
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:46,133
I did it because I just wanted
to help with the case,

171
00:07:46,267 --> 00:07:52,067
or did you just said
that the suspect escaped

172
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:54,733
because of me?

173
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:56,200
Enriquez...

174
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,433
I talked to the Chief.

175
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:01,333
I explained it to him.

176
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:03,733
It's just that...

177
00:08:03,867 --> 00:08:07,700
It's just that you can't
avoid blaming me

178
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:11,367
that the suspect escaped
because of what I did.

179
00:08:15,167 --> 00:08:21,367
Bobby, I don't want to blame you
that a suspect escaped from us.

180
00:08:21,533 --> 00:08:24,333
But look at Noble.

181
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:25,900
Or what if you were
the one who got hurt?

182
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:31,867
For example, you caught up
with him and fought back?

183
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,467
Oh, why?

184
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,300
I can fight for myself.

185
00:08:35,433 --> 00:08:36,700
If you want, we can fight
one-on-one.

186
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:46,367
Bobby, I'm just protecting you
from yourself.

187
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:51,033
Listen to what you're saying.

188
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,567
So maybe it's better...

189
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:59,300
if you get a desk job first.

190
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:00,300
Cool down first.

191
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:06,633
Also, can you listen to me?

192
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:09,667
Because I'm with you in
everything you're going through.

193
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,700
You're with me?

194
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:12,933
With me?

195
00:09:13,067 --> 00:09:16,633
Okay, tell Chief
that you're also at fault,

196
00:09:16,767 --> 00:09:18,600
so we can both have desk jobs.

197
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:21,267
What? Can you do it?

198
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:25,200
Really? You're with me
with what I'm going through?

199
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:35,633
You know, Sir,
I'm grateful to you

200
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:37,367
because I know
you're worried about me.

201
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,200
You're thinking
about my well-being.

202
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,767
But you know, Sir,

203
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:46,033
sometimes, we don't need lessons
and worries.

204
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:49,867
Sometimes, all we need
is an ally.

205
00:10:11,933 --> 00:10:15,233
Niko, do you still
remember me?

206
00:10:15,367 --> 00:10:17,633
I'm Tootsie's friend.

207
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:18,900
Thanks for the sympathies.

208
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:23,067
Take a look at Tootsie.

209
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,533
She's still so beautiful.

210
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:42,367
Well, I really feel like
this is a hate crime.

211
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:45,533
Imagine, second in a row
in the sisterhood

212
00:10:45,667 --> 00:10:47,300
that's been killed.

213
00:10:47,433 --> 00:10:49,267
It's scary.

214
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:51,633
What's their problem with us?

215
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:53,600
We're not doing anything wrong.

216
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:54,767
That's true.

217
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:05,333
In fairness, Madam is beautiful.

218
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:08,167
Don't worry, Tootsie...

219
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,667
We'll hunt down the one
who killed you..

220
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,267
Even if it means our lives
will be in danger.

221
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,700
Even if it means...

222
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,367
Why am I involved?

223
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,800
We are ready to sacrifice
our lives

224
00:11:21,933 --> 00:11:24,533
just to give you justice,
my friend.

225
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:26,467
Hey...

226
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,000
Friend...

227
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:30,867
Do you really need to include me
in your promise?

228
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:34,900
Girl, as far as I know,
I'm just an extended friend.

229
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:37,200
Hey, are you just going to let
our brothers and sisters

230
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:39,900
live in fear?

231
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:43,367
Well, we're just town guards,
Friend.

232
00:11:43,533 --> 00:11:45,767
So let's not give in to fear.

233
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:50,800
I don't have a choice, do I?

234
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,433
- Abdul.
- What is it?

235
00:12:05,567 --> 00:12:08,233
Look at the girl in pink.

236
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:09,633
Who is that?

237
00:12:09,767 --> 00:12:11,200
That's the daughter
of the first victim.

238
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:12,900
She's Zondra's child.

239
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:13,500
Remember?

240
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:17,233
Oh, yes, right?

241
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,500
Wait...

242
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:33,267
Hey, friend, what Mar said
was just a joke.

243
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:37,633
You might haunt me
if I don't keep my promise.

244
00:12:37,767 --> 00:12:39,800
Girl, I'm scared.

245
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:41,833
Please don't do that.

246
00:12:41,967 --> 00:12:43,100
We're friends, right?

247
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,067
Behave.

248
00:12:55,967 --> 00:12:57,433
Jake, I'm going somewhere.

249
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:58,533
I'll go ahead, okay?

250
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:00,400
Where are you going now?

251
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:03,300
Well, I'm investigating
something in Sitio Manggahan.

252
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:04,700
Manggahan?

253
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:06,233
That's a bit far.

254
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:09,500
That's why I had to leave
so I wouldn't be late.

255
00:13:09,633 --> 00:13:11,600
Sorry, I can't come with you.

256
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:12,700
That's okay.

257
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,000
Just wait.

258
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:17,133
Ma'am Bobby, I'll go ahead.

259
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,133
Are you leaving now?

260
00:13:18,267 --> 00:13:19,067
- Yes.
- Oh, okay, okay.

261
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,067
Be careful.

262
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,200
Okay.

263
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,433
Okay.

264
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:26,500
Noble.

265
00:13:26,633 --> 00:13:28,167
- Ma'am?
- Why are you standing doing?

266
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,467
Walk her out?

267
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,333
- Okay.
- Go ahead.

268
00:13:31,467 --> 00:13:32,733
This guy is something else.

269
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,267
Bobby!

270
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,500
You're really busy.

271
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:40,600
What's your assignment?

272
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:45,367
Yeah, you have a desk job.

273
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,800
All homework, that's sad.

274
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:55,167
Lieutenant Samson,
if you don't need me anymore,

275
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:58,267
can you give me a break for now?

276
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,833
I'm not having a good day today.

277
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:02,133
Actually, I need something
from you.

278
00:14:02,267 --> 00:14:04,800
Get me all the files
for robberies and thefts

279
00:14:04,933 --> 00:14:06,600
that have been reported here
at the station

280
00:14:06,733 --> 00:14:08,533
since Mateo Ramos escaped.

281
00:14:10,667 --> 00:14:12,733
Oh, why?

282
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:15,167
You asked, didn't you,
if I needed anything?

283
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:19,267
Well, Chief said
to ask from you.

284
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,500
So is that okay?

285
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:22,733
Can you?

286
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:24,867
Okay.

287
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Bobby...

288
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,400
Get me some coffee first.

289
00:14:30,533 --> 00:14:32,867
Do that first, okay?

290
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
There.

291
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:36,133
Thank you.

292
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:54,600
Hurry up, okay?

293
00:14:58,033 --> 00:14:59,200
How are you, girl?

294
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:02,567
I still can't believe it.

295
00:15:03,767 --> 00:15:08,267
The deaths of Mommy Tootsie
and Zondra were the same.

296
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,267
Do you think so, Marie?

297
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:15,067
Well, in that case,
it looks like a hate crime,

298
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:18,500
and that's what mother's friends
are talking about.

299
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:21,633
Well, if that's the case,
we all need to be careful.

300
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,500
Oh, what's that?

301
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:26,533
What happened to your arm, girl?

302
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:27,733
Oh, this?

303
00:15:27,867 --> 00:15:29,367
- Yes.
- Hey, girl!

304
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,033
Don't say that's
from your boyfriend

305
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:32,367
who's been hurting you.

306
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,800
Oh my, if I were you,
you'd just go with the shibs.

307
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:35,933
You'll be safe.

308
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,133
What's with you?

309
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:39,500
This isn't from my boyfriend.

310
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:41,967
Besides, I don't have
a boyfriend right now.

311
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,633
This is from mother.

312
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:45,233
Zondra?

313
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:47,633
- Is she hurting you?
- Oh my.

314
00:15:47,767 --> 00:15:52,167
Well, I'm a bit troublemaker
and I like to run away.

315
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:55,433
But that's okay.

316
00:15:55,567 --> 00:16:01,667
Mother's hand is really heavy,
but I know that she loves me.

317
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,833
I'm used to it.

318
00:16:17,967 --> 00:16:19,000
Garcia?

319
00:16:19,133 --> 00:16:20,100
Yes, Sir?

320
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:22,367
I have something special
for you to work on.

321
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:27,300
Who else would work on
those special assignments?

322
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:31,900
But special police officers,
right?

323
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:34,767
You always have an answer,
right?

324
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:37,533
Oh, what?

325
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:38,800
No, I don't have an answer.

326
00:16:38,933 --> 00:16:40,267
You're difficult to talk to!

327
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,200
Call Dizon!

328
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:43,867
No, no, Sir,
I mean, you didn't ask,

329
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,400
but I have the answer.

330
00:16:46,533 --> 00:16:48,467
What do you want me to do?

331
00:16:50,867 --> 00:16:55,200
I spoke to Mayor Joaquin
before he died,

332
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:59,667
and he said he had
a strong feeling

333
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:02,400
that Calabari had a new enemy.

334
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:05,367
Does that mean someone has
replaced Victor Santiago?

335
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,467
It's always like that.

336
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,033
When you cut off one head
of a snake,

337
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:12,733
a new one will sprout.

338
00:17:12,867 --> 00:17:15,267
Sometimes two, even three.

339
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:20,633
So I want you to find out
who Calabari's new enemy is.

340
00:17:20,767 --> 00:17:23,100
Yes, Sir.
Don't worry.

341
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:26,567
We'll find that snake
and crush it.

342
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:28,500
You should look
for a partner.

343
00:17:28,633 --> 00:17:32,700
You can choose anyone,
as long as trustworthy.

344
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,667
Anyone? Sir...

345
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,267
I've thought of someone.

346
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,033
- Who?
- It's you.

347
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:39,600
You're really difficult
to talk to.

348
00:17:39,733 --> 00:17:41,700
- I can't! Call Dizon!
- No, Sir.

349
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,900
You're the one who's
difficult to talk to.

350
00:17:43,033 --> 00:17:44,400
You said anyone.

351
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:46,867
But I've already
thought of someone.

352
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,967
It's just my dream to have you
as a partner,

353
00:17:49,133 --> 00:17:50,833
and I can trust you,

354
00:17:50,967 --> 00:17:52,800
but I've already thought
of something else.

355
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:54,033
- Okay, Sir.
- Go ahead.

356
00:17:56,833 --> 00:18:00,567
I still can't stop
thinking about it, Bok.

357
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:01,700
Which one?

358
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:04,633
Are those Alma's visions
you're talking about?

359
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:05,933
Yes, Bok.

360
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:09,167
Because what she told me
came true.

361
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:12,433
It was a bit vague at first,
but when it happened,

362
00:18:12,567 --> 00:18:14,600
what she wanted to say
became clear.

363
00:18:14,733 --> 00:18:16,133
I don't know, okay?

364
00:18:16,267 --> 00:18:18,433
There's something called
coincidence,

365
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:22,267
and then there's also
a term called scam.

366
00:18:22,433 --> 00:18:25,333
I didn't want to believe it
at first, either, Bok,

367
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:29,500
but this coincidence
is too much to be a scam.

368
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,567
So you want to talk to Alma?

369
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:36,200
This killer has two victims.

370
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:40,267
So, where can we find a lead
or help?

371
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,633
Let's figure it out.

372
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:43,700
Let's go.

373
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:56,433
Here's what you've asked
from me, Lieutenant Samson.

374
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,133
You know, Bobby...

375
00:18:58,267 --> 00:19:01,933
I seem to like this Station.

376
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:03,800
Where's Lieutenant Conde?

377
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:08,867
Maybe the news is true, right?

378
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,567
That you two had a fight.

379
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:13,933
Why? Are you together?

380
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:14,700
So, what's this?

381
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,633
It's like you're having an LQ?

382
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:19,000
It's only your first day here,
Lieutenant Samson,

383
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,100
and you're gossiping
right away?

384
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:23,667
Oh, no. The news just came to me
out of the blue.

385
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,733
You know, Bobby, I just want
to give you some advice.

386
00:19:25,867 --> 00:19:30,333
If you really like Tonyo,
don't be too fuzzy, okay?

387
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:34,667
Because Tonyo might find someone
better than you,

388
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:37,800
especially since I'm here.

389
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:40,900
Thanks, Sergeant.

390
00:19:47,467 --> 00:19:50,267
Ma'am Bobby, looks like
Lieutenant Samson

391
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,600
is taunting you again.

392
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,267
Never mind her.

393
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,667
Oh my, she'll tease you
even more.

394
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:57,767
You won't be able to solve
any case

395
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,233
if you're here at the precinct.

396
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,333
Okay, Ma'am, I'll just
attend to something.

397
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,267
Anybody home?

398
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,833
Alma!

399
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,733
This is Tonyo.

400
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,000
- Bok...
- Anybody home?

401
00:20:20,133 --> 00:20:21,700
It looks like
there's no one here.

402
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:30,400
Excuse me,
what are you doing here?

403
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:31,500
Alma...

404
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:34,133
Can we talk?

405
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:36,267
I don't want this anymore, okay?

406
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:37,500
I don't want it anymore.

407
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:40,967
I feel like you're just
enjoying my powers.

408
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,433
Why do you call them powers?

409
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:43,600
Shouldn't it be a curse?

410
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:46,100
Who are you?

411
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,633
By the way, Alma, my partner.

412
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:51,667
Lieutenant Fred Dizon.

413
00:20:53,133 --> 00:20:54,500
Sorry, I don't want
to offend you,

414
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:57,900
but I just don't want
any triggers.

415
00:20:58,033 --> 00:21:01,167
Do you get triggered when
you're touching something?

416
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:02,567
I don't know!

417
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:07,433
It's just that sometimes
when I'm holding a random thing,

418
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,567
sometimes it's like
I'm having a daydream.

419
00:21:11,567 --> 00:21:17,200
Alma, what you said about
neon lights and stilettos?

420
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:18,133
It came true!

421
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:21,100
Oh no!

422
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:22,833
I don't want this, okay?

423
00:21:22,967 --> 00:21:25,100
I don't want this!
I want to be in peace!

424
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:27,100
I want to have a peaceful life!

425
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:28,233
Do you understand?

426
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:33,033
Alma, wait a minute! Please!

427
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:34,467
We're begging you.

428
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:35,867
You don't understand me!

429
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,833
You don't know how I feel!

430
00:21:37,967 --> 00:21:42,633
How about you? You're dreaming
about that heinous crime,

431
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,433
and then you find out
it came true?

432
00:21:45,567 --> 00:21:46,833
How hard it is!

433
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:50,067
I feel like I'm guilty!

434
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,900
I didn't mean for this
to happen!

435
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:55,833
Alma, believe me.

436
00:21:55,967 --> 00:22:00,300
No matter how you look at it,
you're not guilty.

437
00:22:00,433 --> 00:22:04,900
So help us so that there
won't be more victims.

438
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:10,500
If anyone should be
guilty here, it's me.

439
00:22:10,633 --> 00:22:12,667
Because you did your job.

440
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,733
Your prediction came true
at the Stiletto Comedy Bar.

441
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:21,733
I was the one who failed,
and a comedian died.

442
00:22:26,667 --> 00:22:28,600
So help us.

443
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:30,733
We need your help.

444
00:22:30,867 --> 00:22:36,900
Because I have a hunch
this killer has another victim.

445
00:22:37,033 --> 00:22:38,433
Your hunch is right, Tonyo.

446
00:22:40,333 --> 00:22:41,267
What?

447
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,367
What do you mean?

448
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:48,167
I saw something in my vision
that there's another victim.

449
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:17,133
Our mission is to find out
who let Mando escape.

450
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:19,700
One of our jail guards
was involved.

451
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:21,767
Mando gave him P100,000.

452
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,133
How did Mando get
that much money?

453
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:27,667
Glen, he's the one I told you
that's my plus one.

454
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,800
We really need to do
something, Abdul.

455
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:32,467
Even if there's a risk that
we'll be targeted by the killer?

456
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,867
Because if he really
victimizes gays

457
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,367
due of a hate crime,
we are all in danger.

458
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:39,933
It's either a cheater,
an abusive parent,

459
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:40,900
or a swindler.

460
00:23:41,033 --> 00:23:42,667
That seems to be
the killer's pattern.

461
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:43,700
Not just gay!

462
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:45,567
What did you see
in your visions, Alma?

463
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,100
I saw a rainbow.

464
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:48,733
I also saw a street sign.

465
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:50,567
What's written
on the street sign?
